	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 25th 6:01 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just got this Hammer 3 nights ago for my level 11 Woodelf Druid and man I love it.&nbsp;&nbsp;Already I hit for 25+ compared to my max hit of 14.<br>Two KEY notes if you attempt to get this awesome hammer.  1) make sure you pratically max out your 2H-blunt. (you WILL miss alot and the 50 attack delay is a killer for recovery time.)<br>2) Make sure your around level 9 to make this journy.  Alot people will say that you can make this long trip earlier.  I don't recommend it. West and East commens are very dangerous and without CAMO on, you can take a nasty beating.<br><br>ADVICE: If you are starting in Kelthin (woodelf city), I would recommend hanging out near the Orc lift to ask for a Port to Karanas (two zones away from Qeynos)  Fight orcs for a while until someone is actually heading that direction.  Fast forward to Qeynos. Once you arrive in Qeynos, BIND at the front gate.  After you bind, head on over to meet Trumpy(he's a push over..  really easy to beat).  Once beheaded, go back out to the front gate of Qeynos and ask for a port to either West Commens or ButcherBlock(BB). Almost always someone is heading to WC so the trip won't take quite as long.  If you get a port to BB, great!  your done!. Most likely you'll get a port to WC.  Once arrived, CAMO yourself to be hidden from the baddies and head over to EAST commenlands. 90% of the time someone is porting over to BB so just head over to the Desert entrance for a quick and easy port. (I've done this quest now 3 times and every time I've gotten a port within 5-10 minutes of entering EW)<br><br>Tipping: for each port you do, I recommend a 1-2 plat donation.<br><br>Note to Druids: Once you turn in your Head to Bloodforge in South Kadlim and get the Hammer. GATE BACK to Qeynos to go kill Trumpy again.  Why?? because you can SELL your Bloodforge hammer for an easy 25-40 plat to low-mid level characters.  And because you have the head resting in your Bank, hand it over again AFTER you sell your hammer.  This more than covers the cost of the trip and gets you some cash too!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
